addReserves(uint256).details: Adding tokens to the token reserve and C0 Bucket without minting any token. Could revert.

alterRedeemRequestAmount(bool,uint256).details: Alters the redeem amount position for the redeemer

params.delta: the amount to add/substract to current position
params.isAddition: true if adding amount to redeem, false to substract.

calculateRiskProHoldersInterest().details: Calculates RiskPro holders holder interest by taking the total amount of RBCs available on Bucket 0. RiskPro interests = Nb (bucket 0) * riskProRate.

dailyInratePayment().details: Moves the daily amount of interest rate to C0 bucket

evalLiquidation(uint256).details: Evaluates if liquidation state has been reached and runs liq if that's the case

getAllowance(address).details: Returns the amount of token reserve an account is allowed to use for deposit.
getAllowance(address).return: The minimum value between MoC allowance for that account and the account's balance.

getRedeemRequestAt(uint256).details: Gets the RedeemRequest at the queue index position
getRedeemRequestAt(uint256).return: redeemer's address and amount he submitted

initialize(address).details: This initialize replaces the constructor but it is not called automatically. It is necessary because of the upgradeability of the contracts

initialize(address,address).details: This initialize replaces the constructor but it is not called automatically. It is necessary because of the upgradeability of the contracts. Either this function or the next can be used

params._governor: The address that will define when a change contract is authorized to do this unstoppable/stoppable again
params._stopper: The address that is authorized to stop this contract

initialize(address,address,bool).details: This initialize replaces the constructor but it is not called automatically. It is necessary because of the upgradeability of the contracts. Either this function or the previous can be used

params._governor: The address that will define when a change contract is authorized to do this unstoppable/stoppable again
params._stoppable: Define if the contract starts being unstoppable or not
params._stopper: The address that is authorized to stop this contract

isBucketLiquidationReached(bytes32).details: Checks if bucket liquidation is reached.
isBucketLiquidationReached(bytes32).return: true if bucket liquidation is reached, false otherwise

isSettlementEnabled().details: Returns true if blockSpan number of blocks has pass since last execution

mintRiskPro(uint256).details: Mints RiskPro and pays the comissions of the operation.

params.resTokensToMint: Amount Reserve Tokens to spend in minting

mintStableToken(uint256).details: Mint StableToken tokens and pays the commisions of the operation

pause().details: Should only be called by the pauser and when it is stoppable

payRiskProHoldersInterestPayment().details: Pays the RiskPro interest and transfers it to the address mocInrate.riskProInterestAddress RiskPro interests = Nb (bucket 0) * riskProRate.

redeemAllStableToken().details: Allow redeem on liquidation state, user StableTokens get burned and he receives the equivalent ReserveTokens if can be covered, or the maximum available*

redeemFreeStableToken(uint256).details: Redeems the requested amount for the msg.sender, or the max amount of free stableTokens possible.

redeemRiskPro(uint256).details: Redeems RiskPro Tokens and pays the comissions of the operation in ReserveTokens

redeemRiskProx(bytes32,uint256).details: Redeems RiskProx Tokens and pays the comissions of the operation in ReserveTokens

params.bucket: Bucket to reedem, for example X2

redeemStableTokenRequest(uint256).details: Creates or updates the amount of a StableToken redeem Request from the msg.sender

params.stableTokenAmount: Amount of StableTokens to redeem on settlement [using mocPrecision]

sendToAddress(address,uint256).details: Public function to extract and send tokens from the reserve. Will return false if transfer reverts or fails.

params.receiver: Account to which the tokens will be send

sendToAddress(address,uint256).return: False if RRC20 transfer fails or revert and true if succeeds*

params.burnoutAddress: Address to which the funds will be sent on liquidation.

stableTokenAmountToRedeem(address).details: returns the total amount of StableTokens in the redeem queue for redeemer

changeIGovernor(address).notice: Change the contract's governor. Should be called through the old governance system

initialize(address).notice: Initialize the contract with the basic settings

initialize(address,address).notice: Initialize the contract with the basic settings

initialize(address,address,bool).notice: Initialize the contract with the basic settings

makeStoppable().notice: Switches ON the stoppability of the contract; if the contract was paused before making it unstoppable it will be paused again after calling this function

makeUnstoppable().notice: Switches OFF the stoppability of the contract; if the contract was paused it will no longer be so

pause().notice: Called by the owner to pause, triggers stopped state

setStopper(address).notice: Changes the address which is enable to stop this contract

unpause().notice: Called by the owner to unpause, returns to normal state
